  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and a screening sensitivity exercise was conducted during model development to rank input parameters by influence on the hemolysis index — however all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-operating-conditions"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-bench",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis index validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark. Predictions fall within 30% of measured values at 3 of 5 operating points; remaining 2 points exceed acceptable error bounds. Validation activity conducted at conditions partially representative of VAD operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study for centrifugal pump impeller region",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed for three mesh refinement levels. Discretization error estimated at 8.4% for hemolysis index QoI. GCI study meets procedural requirements but achieved level remains below MRL 5 threshold due to unresolved near-wall shear layer uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-monte-carlo-uq",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "1000-sample Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty, blood viscosity variability, and power-law hemolysis model coefficients. 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction interval reported. A screening sensitivity analysis was performed prior to the Monte Carlo runs to identify the three dominant uncertainty contributors (hemolysis model exponent, shear stress threshold, and inlet flow waveform shape); these findings informed the Monte Carlo parameter space but the screening results were not formally archived as a structured sensitivity analysis node in the evidence package."
    }
  ],
